04/02/2004
BUCHAREST, Romania -- Valeriu Steriu, State Secretary with the Ministry of Agriculture, Forestry, Waters and Environment, announced Tuesday (3 February) the country must invest nearly 30 billion euros in environmental protection through 2021, to meet EU standards. 
Half of those funds would have to come from international donors.
In other news Tuesday, Romania signed a nuclear agreement with South Korea, spelling out co-operation in the areas of research and industrial use of nuclear power. 
(Rompres, Mediafax - 04/02/04)
